IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Texas Title X grantee committed to the provision of affordable, confidential, high-quality family planning services.
IRS990.MissionDesc: Women's Health and Family Planning Association of Texas ("WHFPT") is dedicated to the belief that all Texans deserve the right to determine the number, timing and spacing of their children through access to affordable, confidential, high-quality family planning services.
IRS990.Desc: Womens Health and Family Planning Association of Texas (WHFPT) is a nonprofit organization founded in 1977, dedicated to the idea that Texans, regardless of financial or insurance status, should have equal access to high-quality reproductive services and control of the timing and spacing of their children. In early 2013, WHFPT became the sole Title X grantee for the State of Texas.Title X is the only program in Texas through which minors can receive confidential family planning services. Core Title X family planning services include reproductive life plan counseling (or education on pregnancy planning or prevention), contraceptive services, pregnancy testing and counseling, help achieving pregnancy, basic infertility services, HIV screening, STI testing and treatment and preconception health services. WHFPT provided funding to 28 agencies and 94 service sites during the year ended March 31, 2018.In the fifth year of its Title X Project WHFPT, through its subrecipient agencies, provided Title X funded family planning and related services to nearly 195,000 low-income and uninsured Texans.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Women's Health and Family Planning Association of Texas ("WHFPT") shall monitor programmatic and fiscal operations of the sub-recipients as they relate to the project and/or provision of project services, and shall have the right to require sub-recipients to implement reasonable changes to such operations based on WHFPT's findings based on information obtained as a result of WHFPT program staff's contact with sub-recipient, including site visits, chart audits, and review of financial and patient data. WHFPT may recommend appropriate technical assistance and/or training. WHFPT shall work with sub-recipient to obtain required and/or requested technical assistance/or training at no or minimal cost to the sub-recipient.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Form 990 is reviewed by the CEO and the Controller. A copy of the complete Form 990 is distributed to all the board members via e-mail prior to filing the Form 990.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Officers , directors, and key employees are required to disclose annually interest that could give rise to conflicts. The organization regularly and consistently monitors and enforces compliance with the policy.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Board of Trustees conducts an annual CEO performance evaluation and sets annual salary.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The organization makes its governing documents and financial statements available to the public upon request and makes audited financial statements and form 990s available on its website.
